{
  "texts": [
    "This presents two major limitations for this task.",
    "First, the rough action level causes the location model to over-adapt to high-level contextual information while ignoring the atomic action details in the video.",
    "Secondly, the rough action class usually leads to the fuzzy annotation of the time boundary, which is unsuitable for temporal action detection.",
    "To address these issues, Liu et al.",
    "developed a new large-scale fine-grained video dataset called FineAction for temporal action detection."
  ]
}